Paul Sturrock experienced a baptism of fire at Yeovil , as they were relegated for the second consecutive time in his first game in charge - two days after he got the job . The 58-year-old spent four days as an advisor to Conference side Torquay before jumping ship to join League One basement side Yeovil on Thursday . Sturrock has been promoted five times as a manager but Yeovil 's 1-1 draw with fellow strugglers Notts County condemned them to relegation at Huish Park . Yeovil Town manager Paul Sturrock suffered relegation with the club in only his second day in charge . County defender Haydn Hollis headed into his own net to give the hosts the lead but the visitors , in new boss Ricardo Moniz 's first match , equalised through Garry Thompson . The Glovers were tipped for promotion this season but instead , despite stopping a run of six consecutive losses , become the first League One side to be relegated . Garry Thompson 's equaliser condemned the Glovers to back-to-back relegations .